As the year 2022 sets in, expectations are high from the perspective of the regulator and in the other hand from the insurance operators. Although, the National Insurance Commission (NAICOM) is yet to present its programmes of action for the New Year, the industry stakeholders expectedly are awaiting such regulatory directives. Also the market operators are looking forward to seeing the Commission take necessary action against the unhealthy competition which according to them is ruining the industry adding that as the industry welcomes a new business year with high expectation NAICOM, which is yet to unveil its regulatory agenda for the year, should take heed to come up with initiatives that would have a smooth sail through acceptance by all and sundry. PTAD Uses Repatriated N19.610bn To Fund Pension Liability Great Nigeria Insurance Re-Enacts Commitment To Excellence Inâ€¦ Analysts opined that unprofessional practices like price wars, rate cutting, returned premium among others have retrogressed the premium growth of the industry placing operating firms in weak position that incapacitated them from paying genuine claims, a development which weakens public confidence in the industry and tarnishes the overall image. Closely connected to this is the issue of non-payment of claims by some operating firms including the big players noting that NAICOM has been warning such operators but because no punitive action has been taken against any firm, the situation has persisted. Also expecting is an improvement on insurance penetration which has been the bane of the industry over the years, positing that the relaunch of enforcement of compliance with the compulsory insurances according to the Market Development and Restructuring Initiatives (MDRI) would help improve the penetration rate.